<section xmlns="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/dc-library" xmlns:codified="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" containing-doc="D.C. Code">
  <num>50-2513</num>
  <heading>Tax exemption.</heading>
  <para>
    <num>(a)</num>
    <text>Bonds issued by the Authority and the interest thereon are exempt from District taxation except estate, inheritance, and gift taxes.</text>
  </para>
  <para>
    <num>(b)</num>
    <text>Real and personal property owned and used for exempt purposes by the Authority shall be exempt from District taxation.</text>
  </para>
  <annotations>
    <annotation doc="D.C. Law 10-153" type="History" path="§14">Aug. 23, 1994, D.C. Law 10-153, § 14, 41 DCR 4652</annotation>
